definition: Dayi county in Chengdu 成都[Cheng2 du1], Sichuan
big/huge/large/major/great/wide/deep/older (than)/oldest/eldest/greatly/very much/(dialect) father/father's elder or younger brother

sentences.english: IN DAYI COUNTY, Chinese tourists stroll through the meandering courtyards of a rural mansion.
sentences.chinese: 在大邑縣，中國遊客在蜿蜒曲折的鄉間大宅院中漫步。

sentences.english: I was in Dayi County , I love my home.
sentences.chinese: 我是大邑縣人，我很愛我的家鄉。
